        "description": "{\"blocks\":[{\"key\":\"52u5c\",\"text\":\"If your computer can store 500 GB of information, that means you can only play 5 video games of 100 GB. This is a problem right? Most people would choose to buy more disk space. However some mathematicians chose not to buy more space, but to use that same space more smartly. This is called Data Compression in information theory. \",\"type\":\"unstyled\",\"depth\":0,\"inlineStyleRanges\":[],\"entityRanges\":[],\"data\":{}},{\"key\":\"21glt\",\"text\":\"In the english language there are some letters that come after some others quite frequently. For example, 'q' is followed mostly by 'u'. So, a good data compression algorithm would get rid of the 'u's after the 'q's when compressing data to store How to Kill a Mockingbird, for example. \",\"type\":\"unstyled\",\"depth\":0,\"inlineStyleRanges\":[{\"offset\":247,\"length\":27,\"style\":\"ITALIC\"}],\"entityRanges\":[],\"data\":{}},{\"key\":\"2k90v\",\"text\":\"Data compression algoritms analyze the probability of certain sequences of 1s and 0s after other sequences and remove what is unnecessary.\",\"type\":\"unstyled\",\"depth\":0,\"inlineStyleRanges\":[],\"entityRanges\":[],\"data\":{}}],\"entityMap\":{}}",
