        "description": "{\"blocks\":[{\"key\":\"731ep\",\"text\":\"The book Blindness by José Saramago makes a very interesting point. Why do funerals only take place during the day? It is almost sacred to do so. We are even scared by the thought of burying the dead during the night. I think this happens because we need to make sure we recognize the dead. We need to asociate an identity, and we can only do so by actualy looking at that person. \",\"type\":\"unstyled\",\"depth\":0,\"inlineStyleRanges\":[{\"offset\":9,\"length\":9,\"style\":\"ITALIC\"}],\"entityRanges\":[],\"data\":{}}],\"entityMap\":{}}",
