        "description": "{\"blocks\":[{\"key\":\"dpfp2\",\"text\":\"Lambe Lambe is a way of using objects to convey an idea. It is a small universe created by someone in which no words are meant to be spoken. Just as in the photo, the author is always presenting its work to one spectator at a time. The spectator asumes a \\\"spying\\\" role, one in which he/she is completely immersed in the author's universe, and they begin communicating through the objects solely. The author is forced to \\\"watch through the objects' eyes\\\" and has to come up a with a story in which the movements and sounds are imposed by the materials. Every show is different, and the relation between author-spectator is one of intimacy. One can literally hear each other's breathing. \",\"type\":\"unstyled\",\"depth\":0,\"inlineStyleRanges\":[],\"entityRanges\":[],\"data\":{}},{\"key\":\"231ep\",\"text\":\"In this universe, we are forced to stop thinking of ideas through linguistics, and allow ourselves to feel through the objects's language. \",\"type\":\"unstyled\",\"depth\":0,\"inlineStyleRanges\":[],\"entityRanges\":[],\"data\":{}}],\"entityMap\":{}}",
