        "description": "{\"blocks\":[{\"key\":\"cjc7p\",\"text\":\"In Chapter 2 of the book Behave by the neuroscientist Robert Sapolski, the frontal fortex is presented. It is the brain region that makes us be social beings. It deals with impulse control and with decision making. It distinguishes our species from the rest. However, it turns off while we dream and while we have an orgasm.\",\"type\":\"unstyled\",\"depth\":0,\"inlineStyleRanges\":[{\"offset\":25,\"length\":7,\"style\":\"ITALIC\"},{\"offset\":268,\"length\":55,\"style\":\"BOLD\"}],\"entityRanges\":[],\"data\":{}},{\"key\":\"5c1u1\",\"text\":\"Why does this happen? the book does not provide further insight but I find very interesting that we lose our sociality when we have orgasms. \",\"type\":\"unstyled\",\"depth\":0,\"inlineStyleRanges\":[],\"entityRanges\":[],\"data\":{}}],\"entityMap\":{}}",
