        "domain": "ZDu2iGxycCwttZhsYO02",
        "description": "On one airplane flight, I was sitting next to an old man and his wife. It was getting late and the lights dimmed. However, the entertainment screen in front of me remained bright as ever. When I tried turning it off, the old man told me he had tried and that it couldn't be done. I understood and slept with the light. When I woke up I saw some screens that were turned off and I began trying again. After a while, I figured it out and I was able to turn it off. I learned that one should doubt other people's experiences, because the fact that other people fail doesn't mean one must fail. Figuring stuff by ourselves is much more meaningful.",
