        "description": "{\"blocks\":[{\"key\":\"1nsal\",\"text\":\"In his book Imagine, Johan Lehrer explains how creativity arises in improvisation. He introduces a violin performer that explains that he feels himself as a host when improvising, because his main purpose is to transmit feelings. He embraces mistakes by \\\"smiling\\\" at them, by not judging himself but rather letting go so that he is able to tranmit his feelings accordingly. He explains that paying too much attention to your mistakes makes you incapable of entering a flow state.\",\"type\":\"unstyled\",\"depth\":0,\"inlineStyleRanges\":[{\"offset\":12,\"length\":9,\"style\":\"ITALIC\"},{\"offset\":307,\"length\":10,\"style\":\"ITALIC\"}],\"entityRanges\":[],\"data\":{}}],\"entityMap\":{}}"
