        "fileName": "",
        "description": "{\"blocks\":[{\"key\":\"1qlin\",\"text\":\"In his book Imagine, Johan Lehrer explains how Bob Dylan's masterpiece Like a Rolling Stone was created. Dylan had hit a dead end with his work and decided to give up on being a musician. He wanted to write a novel, despite criticism. He got tired of it all and decided to isolate from society. In his room, he began writing his new novel. He wasn't thinking in anything in particular, but rather \\\"letting his pencil do the work\\\". He described the process as a ghost that came in and wrote for him. When he finished he knew he had created a masterpiece and decided to continue his carreer as a musician.\",\"type\":\"unstyled\",\"depth\":0,\"inlineStyleRanges\":[{\"offset\":12,\"length\":9,\"style\":\"ITALIC\"},{\"offset\":71,\"length\":20,\"style\":\"ITALIC\"}],\"entityRanges\":[],\"data\":{}}],\"entityMap\":{}}",
