        "title": "Projection of Leftovers: a new approach on learning",
        "fileName": "",
        "explanation": "{\"blocks\":[{\"key\":\"4jkvj\",\"text\":\"In the lesson 'Lost Arts' breathing was left out of the medical picture. In the lesson 'Presocratics way of philosophy', the study of nature was left out of the philosophical picture. This means that sometimes arts and domains take paths or turns that leave parts that may be important to the field. Breathing the right way may cure diseases and stuying physics can solve metaphysical problems.\",\"type\":\"unstyled\",\"depth\":0,\"inlineStyleRanges\":[],\"entityRanges\":[],\"data\":{}},{\"key\":\"eki2i\",\"text\":\"I propose a new methodology of studying a field: projection of leftovers. In this new way of learning, one must not start, say, programming, by learning about classes, functions, atributes, logic, etc. But should start by understanding the origins of programming, its paradigm. By understanding it as a languaje between man and machine. This investigation, however, must not be passive. One must discern and discover which turns were taken on the field that left important parts behind. From this viewpoint, one must project these leftovers and propose new ways of applying them. \",\"type\":\"unstyled\",\"depth\":0,\"inlineStyleRanges\":[{\"offset\":222,\"length\":25,\"style\":\"BOLD\"},{\"offset\":366,\"length\":19,\"style\":\"BOLD\"},{\"offset\":508,\"length\":16,\"style\":\"BOLD\"}],\"entityRanges\":[],\"data\":{}},{\"key\":\"cgur4\",\"text\":\"We must visualize fields as an accidental 'state of the art' and should be prepared to transform its pilars and foundations.\",\"type\":\"unstyled\",\"depth\":0,\"inlineStyleRanges\":[],\"entityRanges\":[],\"data\":{}}],\"entityMap\":{}}",
